: solid; background-color: #ccc;">Byrne Hobart writes</a>: =E2=80=9CCrypto =
is <em>incredibly</em> well-contained,=C2=A0in that there are giant compani=
es that do crypto (and almost nothing else), and there are giant companies =
with massively diversified portfolios that have a tiny slice of crypto.=E2=
=80=9D There may be systemic risks=C2=A0<em>within crypto</em>, but it=E2=
=80=99s hard to see how they could be systemic risks to the rest of the eco=
nomy.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Also, on the claim that =E2=80=9Cpriv=
ately produced monies are not an effective medium of exchange because they =
